s3TrCommonBoardTable.name: s3TrCommonBoardTable
s3TrCommonBoardTable.description: Information maintained for each token ring board. The information can be retrieved for any token ring board, even if the board is not on the same backplane ring as this NMM. The instance is the slot number of the concentrator that the board occupies.

s3TrCommonBoardEntry.name: s3TrCommonBoardEntry
s3TrCommonBoardEntry.description: There is one entry per board in this table.

s3TrCommonBoardIndex.name: s3TrCommonBoardIndex
s3TrCommonBoardIndex.description: A unique value for each board. Its value ranges between 1 and 12. The value for each board must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization. If a board is inserted or reinserted in a concentrator then the NMM has to be reinitialized.

s3TrCommonBoardRing1or2.name: s3TrCommonBoardRing1or2
s3TrCommonBoardRing1or2.description: Determines which ring the board is currently using on the concentrator backplane.

s3TrCommonBoardRingSpeed.name: s3TrCommonBoardRingSpeed
s3TrCommonBoardRingSpeed.description: Token Ring speed of the ring that this board is connected to.

s3TrPortTable.name: s3TrPortTable
s3TrPortTable.description: A table containing information about each port of a LattisNet concentrator. The number of entries is given by knowing the number of occupied slots in s3ChassisSlotConfigTable whose s3SlotModuleType is of a token ring type and is on the same physical ring as the agent NMM.

s3TrPortEntry.name: s3TrPortEntry
s3TrPortEntry.description: A port entry containing objects at the port level for a particular port.

s3TrPortBoardIndex.name: s3TrPortBoardIndex
s3TrPortBoardIndex.description: A unique value for each board. Its value ranges between 1 and 12. The value for each board must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization. If a board is inserted or reinserted in a concentrator then the NMM has to be reinitialized.

s3TrPortIndex.name: s3TrPortIndex
s3TrPortIndex.description: A unique value for each port. Its value ranges between 1 and 12. The value for each port must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization. If the board is an NMM board it will only have 2 ports, with Port 1 being for Ring In and Port 2 being for Ring Out.

s3TrPortWrap.name: s3TrPortWrap
s3TrPortWrap.description: Status of the port. Setting wrap(2) disconnects the port from the ring and setting this object to connect(3) connects the port to the ring.

s3TrPortTestLatch.name: s3TrPortTestLatch
s3TrPortTestLatch.description: Status of the test latch which is used to set the channel decoder used to monitor the health of the communication path between the NMM and the module channel.

s3TrPortRelayStatus.name: s3TrPortRelayStatus
s3TrPortRelayStatus.description: Status of the channel's present relay mode. On(2) means the channel is in the ring and off(3) means the channel is bypassed.

s3TrPortPhantomStatus.name: s3TrPortPhantomStatus
s3TrPortPhantomStatus.description: Status of the ring access request signal.

s3TrPortPhantomChangeFlag.name: s3TrPortPhantomChangeFlag
s3TrPortPhantomChangeFlag.description: Change(3) indicates that port phantom has been changed from OFF to ON. After inquiry by NMS, it will be cleared to noChange(2). Port phantom changing from ON to OFF has no impact on this object.

s3TrPortChgSyn2IBM.name: s3TrPortChgSyn2IBM
s3TrPortChgSyn2IBM.description: If the port is on a ring in/ring out module this object changes the strap state depending on the jumper setting retrieved as s3TrPortStrap. If the strap is set for SynOptics phantom option, this object can be changed to ibm(3). If the strap is set for non-SynOptics option, this object can not be changed. Non ring in/ring out modules or fiber ring in/ring out modules must take on the value of notSupported(1).

s3TrPortStrap.name: s3TrPortStrap
s3TrPortStrap.description: If the port is on a ring in/ring out module this object signifies whether the hardware jumper is in synoptics(2) mode or ibm(3) mode. This information is retrieved using a NMI command. For ports on fiber ring in/ring out modules, and those ports not on ring in/ring out modules, the agent always returns notSupported(1).

s3TrNmmFnNum.name: s3TrNmmFnNum
s3TrNmmFnNum.description: Defines the flat network number that this NMM is part of.

s3TrNmmRingNum.name: s3TrNmmRingNum
s3TrNmmRingNum.description: Defines the segment number that this NMM is connected to.

s3TrNmmSlotNum.name: s3TrNmmSlotNum
s3TrNmmSlotNum.description: Defines the slot number that this NMM is connected to. New NMS implementations should use the object s3AgentMySlotId defined in the common MIB.

s3TrNmmFpuIdRev.name: s3TrNmmFpuIdRev
s3TrNmmFpuIdRev.description: The revision of the Front-end Frame Processing unit. 0=Rev. A, 1=Rev. B, etc.

s3TrNmmFpuStatus.name: s3TrNmmFpuStatus
s3TrNmmFpuStatus.description: The status of the Front-end Frame Processing Unit.

s3TrNmmDramSize.name: s3TrNmmDramSize
s3TrNmmDramSize.description: The highest address of the DRAM in the NMM memory map.

s3TrNmmEepromSize.name: s3TrNmmEepromSize
s3TrNmmEepromSize.description: The size of the EEPROM in the NMM memory map.

s3TrNmmGrpAddrFrmsRxOk.name: s3TrNmmGrpAddrFrmsRxOk
s3TrNmmGrpAddrFrmsRxOk.description: Number of Group Address frames received without error by this NMM. Note: The NMM counts only Group Address frames that are addressed to its own Group Address(es).

s3TrNmmRing1or2.name: s3TrNmmRing1or2
s3TrNmmRing1or2.description: Determines which ring the NMM is currently using on the concentrator backplane.

s3TrNmmHexDisplay.name: s3TrNmmHexDisplay
s3TrNmmHexDisplay.description: 4 octet hex display string that is displayed on the NMM control panel.

s3TrNmmEpromSize.name: s3TrNmmEpromSize
s3TrNmmEpromSize.description: The size of the EPROM in the NMM memory map.

s3TrNodeEntry.name: s3TrNodeEntry
s3TrNodeEntry.description: Entry in the table containing counters and profiling information for each node detected on the local token ring.

s3TrNodeEntMacAddress.name: s3TrNodeEntMacAddress
s3TrNodeEntMacAddress.description: MAC address of node that this entry in the table is for.

s3TrNodeEntStatus.name: s3TrNodeEntStatus
s3TrNodeEntStatus.description: Tells whether the station is currently beaconing or not.

s3TrNodeEntNodeStatus.name: s3TrNodeEntNodeStatus
s3TrNodeEntNodeStatus.description: Node status as defined in 802.5 specification (section 3.3.2.18).

s3TrNodeLineErrs.name: s3TrNodeLineErrs
s3TrNodeLineErrs.description: Number of line errors. Section 3.8.1 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeBurstErrs.name: s3TrNodeBurstErrs
s3TrNodeBurstErrs.description: Number of burst errors. Section 3.8.3 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeAriFciErrs.name: s3TrNodeAriFciErrs
s3TrNodeAriFciErrs.description: Number of ARI FCI errors. See AC errors, Section 3.8.4 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeLostFrames.name: s3TrNodeLostFrames
s3TrNodeLostFrames.description: Number of frames lost. Section 3.8.6 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeRcvCongestErrs.name: s3TrNodeRcvCongestErrs
s3TrNodeRcvCongestErrs.description: Number of receive congestion errors. Section 3.8.7 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeFrmCopyErrs.name: s3TrNodeFrmCopyErrs
s3TrNodeFrmCopyErrs.description: Number of frame copy errors. Section 3.8.8 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeTokenErrs.name: s3TrNodeTokenErrs
s3TrNodeTokenErrs.description: Number of token errors. Section 3.8.10 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeInternalErrs.name: s3TrNodeInternalErrs
s3TrNodeInternalErrs.description: Number of internal errors. Section 3.8.2 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeAbortTransErrs.name: s3TrNodeAbortTransErrs
s3TrNodeAbortTransErrs.description: Number of abort delimiter transmitted errors. Section 3.8.5 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeFrequencyErrs.name: s3TrNodeFrequencyErrs
s3TrNodeFrequencyErrs.description: Number of frequency errors. Section 3.8.9 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeEntProductId.name: s3TrNodeEntProductId
s3TrNodeEntProductId.description: A brief string describing the product specified by the vendor. Section 3.3.2.14 of IEEE 802.5 specification. The characters in the string are represented in EBCDIC for IBM products, in ASCII for others.

s3TrNodeEntUna.name: s3TrNodeEntUna
s3TrNodeEntUna.description: The Upstream Neighbor Address. Section 3.3.2.15 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeEntNodeVersion.name: s3TrNodeEntNodeVersion
s3TrNodeEntNodeVersion.description: String that represents the version of the station software. Section 3.3.2.17 of IEEE 802.5 specification. The characters in the string are represented in EBCDIC for IBM products, in ASCII for others.

s3TrNodeEntPhysDrop.name: s3TrNodeEntPhysDrop
s3TrNodeEntPhysDrop.description: This reports the physical location of this node on the ring. Section 3.3.2.13 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeEntFuncAddr.name: s3TrNodeEntFuncAddr
s3TrNodeEntFuncAddr.description: Specifies the functional addresses used by this station. Section 3.3.2.8 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeEntAuthFuncClass.name: s3TrNodeEntAuthFuncClass
s3TrNodeEntAuthFuncClass.description: This specifies the functional classes that are allowed to be active in the station. Section 3.3.2.3 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeEntAuthAccPriority.name: s3TrNodeEntAuthAccPriority
s3TrNodeEntAuthAccPriority.description: The maximum priority this station is allowed to use. Section 3.3.2.2 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeEntGrpAddr.name: s3TrNodeEntGrpAddr
s3TrNodeEntGrpAddr.description: This contains the group address of this station. Section 3.3.2.9 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeEntStationId.name: s3TrNodeEntStationId
s3TrNodeEntStationId.description: This string is used to uniquely identify the station. It may be equal to the station's MAC address. Section 3.3.2.21 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeEntBeaconType.name: s3TrNodeEntBeaconType
s3TrNodeEntBeaconType.description: This specifies the type of beacon frame seen. Section 3.3.2.4 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrNodeBeaconCnt.name: s3TrNodeBeaconCnt
s3TrNodeBeaconCnt.description: Number of beacon frames that have been sent by this station.

s3TrNodeLastBeaconTime.name: s3TrNodeLastBeaconTime
s3TrNodeLastBeaconTime.description: The time of the last beacon frame sent by this station.

s3TrNodeLastInsertTime.name: s3TrNodeLastInsertTime
s3TrNodeLastInsertTime.description: The time of the last ring insertion by this station. Time is relative from the system uptime.

s3TrNodeFirstInsertTime.name: s3TrNodeFirstInsertTime
s3TrNodeFirstInsertTime.description: The time of the first ring insertion by this station. Time is relative from the system uptime.

s3TrNodeLastDeinsertTime.name: s3TrNodeLastDeinsertTime
s3TrNodeLastDeinsertTime.description: The time of the last ring deinsertion by this station. Time is relative from the system uptime.

s3TrNodeRemoveStation.name: s3TrNodeRemoveStation
s3TrNodeRemoveStation.description: Removes the MAC address associated with this entry from the ring by sending a REMOVE MAC frame if this object is written to with remove(2).

s3TrRingFrmsRxOk.name: s3TrRingFrmsRxOk
s3TrRingFrmsRxOk.description: Number of frames received successfully by the NMM.

s3TrRingOctetsRxOk.name: s3TrRingOctetsRxOk
s3TrRingOctetsRxOk.description: Number of octets received successfully by the NMM.

s3TrRingBcastFrmsRxOk.name: s3TrRingBcastFrmsRxOk
s3TrRingBcastFrmsRxOk.description: Number of broadcast frames received successfully by the NMM.

s3TrRingLineErrs.name: s3TrRingLineErrs
s3TrRingLineErrs.description: Number of line errors. Section 3.8.1 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingBurstErrs.name: s3TrRingBurstErrs
s3TrRingBurstErrs.description: Number of burst errors. Section 3.8.3 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingAriFciErrs.name: s3TrRingAriFciErrs
s3TrRingAriFciErrs.description: Number of ARI FCI errors. See AC errors, Section 3.8.4 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingLostFrames.name: s3TrRingLostFrames
s3TrRingLostFrames.description: Number of frames lost. Section 3.8.6 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingRcvCongestErrs.name: s3TrRingRcvCongestErrs
s3TrRingRcvCongestErrs.description: Number of receive congestion errors. Section 3.8.7 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingFrmCopyErrs.name: s3TrRingFrmCopyErrs
s3TrRingFrmCopyErrs.description: Number of frame copy errors. Section 3.8.8 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingTokenErrs.name: s3TrRingTokenErrs
s3TrRingTokenErrs.description: Number of token errors. Section 3.8.10 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingInternalErrs.name: s3TrRingInternalErrs
s3TrRingInternalErrs.description: Number of internal errors. Section 3.8.2 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingAbortTransErrs.name: s3TrRingAbortTransErrs
s3TrRingAbortTransErrs.description: Number of abort delimiter transmitted errors. Section 3.8.5 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingFrequencyErrs.name: s3TrRingFrequencyErrs
s3TrRingFrequencyErrs.description: Number of frequency errors. Section 3.8.9 of IEEE 802.5 specification.

s3TrRingBeaconCnt.name: s3TrRingBeaconCnt
s3TrRingBeaconCnt.description: Number of beacon frames that have been seen.

s3TrRingBeaconType.name: s3TrRingBeaconType
s3TrRingBeaconType.description: This specifies the type of beacon frame seen. Section 3.3.2.4 of IEEE 802.5 Specification.

s3TrRingLastBeaconTime.name: s3TrRingLastBeaconTime
s3TrRingLastBeaconTime.description: The time of the last beacon frame sent on the ring. Time is relative from the system uptime.

s3TrRingBeaconStation.name: s3TrRingBeaconStation
s3TrRingBeaconStation.description: The MAC address of station last beaconing.
